{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 830527, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Robotusch", "body": "A brief overview of the fight:\r\n[b]Phase 1[/b]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Save your cooldowns for phase 3![/li]\r\n[li]Ranged DPS must shoot down the frozen spheres in order to create patches of permafrost.[/li]\r\n[li]Anub'arak will spawn adds throughout the fight that must be tanked on permafrost ground (otherwise they will burrow and respawn with full hp).[/li]\r\n[li]Adds will put a debuff on whoever is tanking it that increases physical damage taken, so DPS needs to burn it down fast. In 25man you will get two adds at a time, and like the Auriaya encounter in Ulduar, the adds will get a buff that increases damage done when they're within 12 yards of each other. So split them up![/li]\r\n[li]Anub'arak will also place a dot on random raid members, but it doesn't do any significant damage (21k damage over 18 seconds)[/li]\r\n[li]After a while, Anub'arak will burrow (and contrary to previous rumors, you can't prevent this from happening by tanking him on Permafrost) and start..[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\n[b]Phase 2[/b]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]A random raid member will be marked with a hunters mark and Anub'arak will only chase him. He will change target occasionally, so keep an eye out for who has it. The raid should watch out for it and NEVER get between the rubble and the marked person, otherwise they'll get impaled[/li]\r\n[li]Impale can and will two-shot people![/li]\r\n[li]Small scarab adds will pop from the ground and chase people around (I'm not sure if they will change target according to threat or if it's a static target) . Every time they hit someone they will stack a debuff on that target, which deals 1000 damage every 3 seconds. This can easily stack up fast and start hurting really bad. However, Rogues can cloak it and I wouldn't be surprised if bubble/iceblock works as well[/li]\r\n[li]After a while, Anub'arak will repop from the ground and resume Phase 1 until he hits 30%, at which point we goes into...[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\n[b]Phase 3[/b]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]No more adds will spawn, so it's important that whatever adds remain alive are killed asap[/li]\r\n[li]Blow heroism/bloodlust and all cooldowns![/li]\r\n[li]Throughout phase 3 the entire raid will be affected by Leeching Swarm, which drains 10% of every raid members [b]current[/b] health per second.[/li]\r\n[li]This will be extremely healing intensive, but healers should not go all out aoe healing. Only heal enough to ensure that people won't die, don't top them off as it will only increase the damage taken[/li]\r\n[/ul]", "date": "2009-09-03T05:09:18-05:00", "rating": 107, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Phase 3 on 10 man is easily covered by 2 HoT healers.  Our setup was a tree and resto shammy.  Keeping a Rejuv on eveyone and chain healing anyone who took spike damage kept our health in the ~30% range so we weren't taking heavy damage, and prevented healing him much.  This fight would probly not be too bad with a disc. priest helping to mitigate some of the damage as well, since ( low health + %based damage = less shield used up)  but i'm not sure if I'd rely on it.  As a somewhat related statement, Blizzard needs to add an effect to the fall to this boss that removes/prevents water walking ", "creationdate": "2009-09-03T05:09:19-05:00", "id": 429988, "rating": 9, "commentid": 830527, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "jaraii", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The water-walking deaths can be avoided by facing your camera into the water, and mouse-running into it... By running towards the water, you sink even with Path of Frost, so don't take fall damage.   Then go nuts at the DK and rez everyone else.", "creationdate": "2009-11-09T19:24:49-06:00", "id": 131624, "rating": 30, "commentid": 830527, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "197806", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "In phase three, if your dps is good enough, you can let the burrowers burrow so the dps can burn down anub'arak before they reemerge", "creationdate": "2010-10-16T10:42:54-05:00", "id": 186937, "rating": 3, "commentid": 830527, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bigmcnuggets", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-09-03T05:12:54-05:00", 2, "Robotusch"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 830590, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "2OfDiamonds", "body": "Don't look so smug! I know what you're thinking, but Azjol-Nerub was merely a set back. \r\nDid you honestly believe I would trust my future to some lowbie 5-man dungeon? \r\nHahahaha... Oh no, no, no, that was merely an instrument, a stepping stone to a much larger plan! \r\nIt has all led to this...and this time, you will not interfere!", "date": "2009-09-03T06:58:12-05:00", "rating": 238, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "And i would have gotten away with it too, if it weren't for you meddling kids!", "creationdate": "2010-06-08T23:38:11-05:00", "id": 167305, "rating": 63, "commentid": 830590, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Xcythe", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "thats a qoute fro kaelthas sunstider in MT isnt it", "creationdate": "2011-09-25T19:30:28-05:00", "id": 266990, "rating": -38, "commentid": 830590, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "883156", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 830802, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "451337", "body": "We did this on 10 man last night, our strategy was slightly different.\r\n\r\nDuring Phase 2 we all stacked on the OT on top of permafrost.  Anub burrows underground and tries to surface under the raid but can't because he gets dazed by the permafrost.  As soon as he got to  us and dazed himself (it's pretty obvious when this happens, ice spikes shoot up) we stayed stacked on the OT, moved to a different permafrost patch and AOE'd the scarab adds down.\r\n\r\nThe advantage to this is that the whole raid is together, this makes it a lot easier to AOE the adds without them chasing a random raid member in a different part of the room.", "date": "2009-09-03T11:57:11-05:00", "rating": 38, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 831280, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "zapiks44", "body": "All those who complained about Anub'arak being reduced to a level 74 5-man dungeon boss, your prayers have been answered.\n\nHe may be easy on the 10 and 25-man normal difficulties, but if the first boss of the heroic versions of Trial of the Crusader is any indication (the DPS requirements are even higher than Algalon), he'll be an absolute nightmare on heroic difficulty. \n\nExactly as he should be :)", "date": "2009-09-03T23:43:50-05:00", "rating": 71, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Kelthuzad lead naxxramas, and anubarak lead trial of the crusader, saphoron also was in naxx, all of arthas' friends from WCIII are done... Arthas s all that's left...", "creationdate": "2010-02-15T21:28:38-06:00", "id": 149379, "rating": 14, "commentid": 831280, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "541042", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-09-03T23:45:49-05:00", 1, "zapiks44"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 831736, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "nekochen", "body": "Hm, Leeching Swarm does 10% remaining HP damage to everyone in the raid, so if we dont heal until the very last minute at like 500-1000hp remaining, the damage done to the person would be trivial almost to none? except the minimal 250 damage which is almost nonexistant at this level.", "date": "2009-09-04T13:47:07-05:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The problem with this is that there [b]might[/b] be DoTs from the adds up and Penetrating Colds [b]will[/b] be going around. If you let the DPS go too low, they'll be killed before your healers can react.  Edit for clarification:  Penetrating Cold: 3500 every 3 seconds. Randomly targeted. DoTs from adds stack as long as the target is getting hit. Depending on when you reach phase 3 these might be still up.  Both of these means that while you [b]can[/b] try letting DPS just drop to very low HP levels, you risk getting them killed when another Penetrating Cold hits. It's much easier to just keep", "creationdate": "2009-09-04T13:47:08-05:00", "id": 423805, "rating": 12, "commentid": 831736, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Jushak", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-09-04T13:47:28-05:00", 1, "nekochen"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 832459, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Calidus", "body": "On heroic mode the adds gain a new ability which needs to be interrupted: [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=66134]Shadow Strike[/url].", "date": "2009-09-05T09:09:23-05:00", "rating": 56, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "For the heroic version of the fight, Paladin tanks with excess amounts of Block (that's right, Block sets aren't just for 5 man heroics anymore!) are GREAT for tanking adds. First, they have Avenger's Shield to silence the mobs - second, they have Holy Wrath for those \"oh SH--\" moments where you know at least one of the adds is going to Shadowstrike.  Good luck on H Anub!", "creationdate": "2010-03-20T19:43:40-05:00", "id": 154929, "rating": 5, "commentid": 832459, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Strudels", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 832762, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "160129", "body": "Looks like someone got bigger and a new paint job. \nNext week on Pimp my Raid Boss, Arthas pimps out Kel'Thuzzad.\n\nEDIT: Spelling Errors", "date": "2009-09-05T15:56:55-05:00", "rating": 144, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Well, I would be very suprised if KT does not show up as a boss in Icecrown Citadel.  After all, you can\u00b4t kill what\u00b4s not alive.", "creationdate": "2009-09-14T04:06:43-05:00", "id": 121909, "rating": 14, "commentid": 832762, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "75972", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Buh, well, Kel'thuzad is already undead..so..he's dead? Oh dear god it's a conumdrum", "creationdate": "2009-09-18T01:33:21-05:00", "id": 122555, "rating": 15, "commentid": 832762, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sallara", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I wouldn't call it \"pimping\" out Kel'Thuzad now that we know the Lich boss in Icecrown is \"Lady Deathwhisper\".", "creationdate": "2009-10-09T10:52:38-05:00", "id": 126575, "rating": 25, "commentid": 832762, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Prada", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=69677]Done.[/url]  apparently he irritated the producers, so they had to pimp him into something more managable.", "creationdate": "2009-11-21T23:05:25-06:00", "id": 133720, "rating": 28, "commentid": 832762, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "jGarand", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Well, liches CAN die, if their [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Phylactery]phylacteries[/url] are destroyed. Almost happened to our animal loving Kel'Thuzad here, if it wasn't because of [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Father_Inigo_Montoy]Father Indigo Montoy[/url].", "creationdate": "2010-06-03T08:58:18-05:00", "id": 166457, "rating": 12, "commentid": 832762, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "nguyenhothanh", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-09-06T02:41:42-05:00", 1, "160129"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 832937, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "tmilhomens", "body": "\"The former king of Azjol-Nerub, Anub'arak was among the nerubians slaughtered in the War of the Spider.One of his most loyal commanders was Anub'Rekhan. Ner'zhul the Lich King raised the high lords of the Spider Kingdom as undead to do his bidding, Anub'arak among them.\r\n\r\nNow as a malicious crypt lord, he is forced to use his powers to purge the snow swept landscape of any remaining resistance to the reign of the Lich King. Despite the pleas from his former subjects, he has been ordered to massacre many nerubians who tried to oppose the undead. \"", "date": "2009-09-05T19:27:09-05:00", "rating": 42, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 833540, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "citrique", "body": "Heroic:\n\n25% more hp.\n\nBurrowers cast shadow strike as mentioned above, needs to be interrupted. Tends to be targeted at the anub tank. Paladin offtank works well.\n\nYou only get 6 orbs total for the entire fight. This basically gives you a max of two underground phases (assuming using 2 permafrost per phase + 1 for adds during the burn phase), if you can't get him to 30% before he burrows a third time, it's probably a wipe.\n\nPermafrost snare is now 80%, not 30%.\n\nBoP works on players affected by the pursued debuff during underground phases. BoP the targeted person to avoid having to waste permafrost. Iceblock and warlock demonic circle are also useful tools for caster dps targeted by him.\n\nSwarm scarabs have 50% more HP. Random scarabs will enrage more often, making them immune to CC and increasing their movement and attack speed. DKs casting chains of ice on them while ranged dps fire nukes works well. Melee dps should not dps them if they're snared as their initial aggro target is random, but when snared they will switch to you if you dps them and having more than a few stacks of their debuff is really nasty for healers.\n\nBurrower adds will continue to spawn at their regular intervals while leeching swarm is active. They will need to be offtanked and ignored. Allowing them to burrow is actually beneficial during this phase to take pressure from the offtank so they can assist in DPSing anub down.\n\nThe berserk timer is 8 minutes, AFAIK, but it really doesn't matter as you will need to force him to 30% a lot sooner.", "date": "2009-09-06T12:47:10-05:00", "rating": 50, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Abilities such as Ice Block, Vanish, and Pally Bubble are actually quite useful in heroic mode. As mentioned, while Anub'arak will switch targets immediately upon casting those spells (except BoP), you could have the rest of the raid stand behind a permafrost so that he runs straight into it upon switching. The benefit of this is that you can have the targeted person run far far away from the raid and have the raid positioned on the other side of the room (behind a permafrost). Upon vanish (etc), Anub'arak will have to travel to the opposite end of the room, resulting in the longest single kit", "creationdate": "2009-09-06T12:47:11-05:00", "id": 424242, "rating": 18, "commentid": 833540, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "RiceCake", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The issue with using immunities/FD/vanish/etc. as part of a repeatable strategy is that you can't ensure he will target one or two people with a way to force a target switch on Anub. That, and he will switch off extremely fast, so if you don't have a proper ice patch down he will probably wind up killing someone. However, you can expect a reasonably balanced group on H-Anub-25 to have three or four BoPs up to do the extended kite thing (which normally just consists of getting the BoP four or five seconds after he targets you, sitting near an ice patch for a bit, and pulling him over it with a ", "creationdate": "2009-09-06T12:47:11-05:00", "id": 427350, "rating": 6, "commentid": 833540, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "238581", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "In addition, rogue could Sprint to far away from raid then Vanish before Anub'arak reaches you. Along with BoP/Ice Block.. all sorts of immunity to save a frost orb.  Please be reminded that Anub'arak's speed is increasing when he is Pursuing someone(speed reset when he hits the ice). By doing this, Anub will be Pursuing someone else in hyper-speed.", "creationdate": "2009-09-07T23:08:09-05:00", "id": 120864, "rating": 7, "commentid": 833540, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Abyssalhand", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "just a note, DO NOT  iceblock, vanish, etc. He will change target and go at full speed towards the next person, and they're not likely to avoid him at the speed he's going at, instant 1 shot on heroic", "creationdate": "2009-09-08T15:22:31-05:00", "id": 120978, "rating": 13, "commentid": 833540, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "241395", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-09-06T12:58:35-05:00", 5, "citrique"]}
