{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 335072, "nreplies": 9, "sticky": 0, "user": "93802", "body": "Anub'arak is a Crypt Lord that accompanies Arthas on his second visit to Northrend when The Icecrown Glacier is under siege by Illidan and his agents, Kael'thas and Lady Vashj.\n\nDuring Arthas' trip through the ruins of Azjol-Nerub, the Nerubians refer to him as the Traitor King. This is because he fought in the War of the Spider as a nerubian, and Ner'zhul and the Lich King later raised several high lords to do their bidding, Anub'arak was on of these and he was reborn as a Crypt Lord. During the final battle in Icecrown, he helps Arthas take control of the four obelisks surrounding Icecrown to open its gates.\n\nNow in Lich King, he will go back to Azjol-Nerub to be it's final boss for the 5 man instance, and he may also make an appearance in the Icecrown Glacier 25-man raid as a boss as well. (He should atleast, I mean... he does deserve it.)", "date": "2008-07-24T14:10:12-05:00", "rating": 94, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Well he might just be raised again or do an 'I must fall back manouver' in live to be a raid boss (AKA he'll pull a Kael on us). I agree he deserves a better placement than this.  another possibility is that he will be swapped out if enough fuss is made and we'll find a different nerubian in his place on live.", "creationdate": "2008-08-29T14:06:40-05:00", "id": 347883, "rating": 4, "commentid": 335072, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "pyrokin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He will, as a final boss in the Argent Coliseum raid.", "creationdate": "2009-06-29T18:18:46-05:00", "id": 106793, "rating": 19, "commentid": 335072, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ryokuga", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "\"Yess, my fine young crusadersss...Azjol-Nerub was merely a sssetback...\"", "creationdate": "2009-06-30T19:05:05-05:00", "id": 106989, "rating": 51, "commentid": 335072, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "192801", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Did you really think chopping off my head and carapace every other day would stop me?", "creationdate": "2009-07-09T19:55:58-05:00", "id": 108764, "rating": 46, "commentid": 335072, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "withmyrice", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "An00b'arak !", "creationdate": "2009-08-20T03:50:15-05:00", "id": 421342, "rating": 4, "commentid": 335072, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Xdoom", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-08-21T22:41:08-05:00", 2, "93802"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 347202, "nreplies": 16, "sticky": 0, "user": "ChrisChaud", "body": "Health: 164,512 HP\n\nAbilities:\n\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?spell=53467]Locust Swarm[/url]: Slows movement speed by 40%.\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?spell=53520]Carrion Beetles[/url]: Summons 2 Carrion Beetles every second for 4 sec.\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?spell=53472]Pound[/url]: Rears up and smashes down on all enemies in front of the caster within 15 yards, dealing 9425 to 10575 damage and pounding them into the floor for 6 sec.\n    * Burrows underground at certain HP intervals (~66%, ~33% and ~15%), becoming invulnerable. While submerged, several things happen:\n          o [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?spell=53454] Impale[/url]:Spikes occasionally shoot up from the ground, knocking players up in the air and causing damage.\n          o Various Nerubian Assassin, Darter, and Guardian mobs spawn and must be killed. Mobs spawn faster as the fight progresses. \n\nConfirmed Loot:\n\n[i]Normal[/i]\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=35663]Charmed Silken Cord[/url] (Cloth Belt)\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=35661]Signet of Arachnathid Command[/url] (Tanking Ring)\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=35662]Wing Cover Girdle[/url] (Mail Belt)\n\n[i]Heroic[/i]\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=37236]Insect Vestments[/url] (Leather Chest)\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=37242]Sash of the Servant[/url] (Cloth Belt)\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=37238]Rod of the Fallen Monarch[/url] (Wand)\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=37235]Crypt Lord's Deft Blade[/url] (Sword)\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=41796]Design: Infused Twilight Opal[/url] (Jewelcrafting Design)\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=37241]Ancient Aligned Girdle[/url] (Plate Belt)\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=37237]Chitin Shell Greathelm[/url] (Plate Head)\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=37232]Ring of the Traitor King[/url] (Caster Ring)\n    * [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=37240]Wing Cover Girdle [/url] (Caster Plate Wrists)\n\n\nThanks to WotLKWiki.info", "date": "2008-08-07T19:19:57-05:00", "rating": 55, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Although he does have a Locust Swarm, the one you linked is from Anub'rekhan, not Anub'arak. Anub'arak's locust swarm is [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?spell=53467]Locust Swarm[/url].", "creationdate": "2008-08-23T17:33:51-05:00", "id": 44245, "rating": 26, "commentid": 347202, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "asktgm", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He burrows, entering phase 2, at 75%, 50%, and 25%.", "creationdate": "2008-10-09T23:20:36-05:00", "id": 49951, "rating": 12, "commentid": 347202, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "ArgentSun", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "His pound ability has a long casting time.  It will hit everyone in a cone in front of him.  You can actually move BEHIND him, even while tanking, and take zero damage from it.  That makes the fight very easy, even on Heroic mode.", "creationdate": "2008-11-15T18:49:28-06:00", "id": 56302, "rating": 30, "commentid": 347202, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Hothgor", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He also summons various mobs, among them the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=29217]Anub'ar Venomancer[/url] is probably the most interesting", "creationdate": "2009-01-05T01:06:03-06:00", "id": 70304, "rating": 6, "commentid": 347202, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "eddu", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I have seen several posts here recommending the tank to run behind him to avoid Pound. I have tried that in the past, but because of bad timing or lag I have seen him turn to follow me and pound the group.  There is an easier way. Just move away from him when he is casting pound and get out of range. Once you are out of range, he stops casting and comes after you.", "creationdate": "2009-02-27T17:30:00-06:00", "id": 82800, "rating": 5, "commentid": 347202, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "330257", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-14T15:20:51-06:00", 3, "ChrisChaud"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 352889, "nreplies": 14, "sticky": 0, "user": "L33tsauce", "body": "Anub'arak as a 5-man boss...\r\n\r\n/shoots self", "date": "2008-08-14T15:59:18-05:00", "rating": 150, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "In defense of Blizzard and those who enjoy the storyline, but aren't in a high-end raiding guild, this is a good opportunity to experience and even become a part of the lore without grinding mindlessly for hours, days, or weeks on end for eternals or rep. I, for one, am glad that I won't have to farm 100 badges for a piece with ever-so-slightly better stats than my current one, or spend hundreds of gold all for new gems (so I can have a .2% change in my hit and def), all just to see, let alone [i]defeat[/i] [b][u]one[/u][/b] recognizable character from WC3.  I feel (and apparently Blizzard agr", "creationdate": "2008-08-14T15:59:19-05:00", "id": 367675, "rating": 72, "commentid": 352889, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Verdice", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "\"without coordinating twenty-four other people who probably don't even know or care about the lore, and just want \"epic lootz\" for their similarly small stat changes/bragging rights.\"  I find above statement quite insulting to be honest. For your information, majority of people I've raided with (and we are talking about varied mix of people, from casual raiders to HC ones) [b]do[/b] know the lore. Hell, some of the people in my guild are the worst \"lore-nerds\" (as they put it themselves) you'll ever find.   While [b]some[/b] people are the way you describe, they are probably a minority in your", "creationdate": "2008-08-14T15:59:19-05:00", "id": 391534, "rating": 23, "commentid": 352889, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Jushak", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Indeed, its a bit unfair, all bosses from Warcraft 3 have a Boss statute and a \"?\" level, and they reside in at least 25-man, and him, a 74 Elite, in 5-man...  /rude Blizzard  (I'm sorry if I insulted someone)", "creationdate": "2008-10-24T05:08:14-05:00", "id": 52365, "rating": 85, "commentid": 352889, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Slycopperr", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "what an outrage, that Anub'Arak be a minor boss like that he was my favorite character in Warcraft 3, and to see him sink to this level is repulsive", "creationdate": "2008-11-13T21:27:47-06:00", "id": 55901, "rating": 59, "commentid": 352889, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "229530", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It's a shame that he doesn't have his original voice from Warcraft 3: The Frozen Throne..", "creationdate": "2009-02-23T11:34:31-06:00", "id": 81996, "rating": 35, "commentid": 352889, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Arkmage", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
