{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 395631, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ingolfur", "body": "When I first heard about WotLK and that Naxx 2 would come, I thought to myself \"They'll surely make Anub'arak the penultimate boss of Icecrown\".... And when I found out about him being a lvl 74 5 man \"boss\"? That's like....the stupidest thing they've done so far in my opinion. -.-  Seriously, what made them think \"We'll make him something that players that have never played through the TFT campaign just totally forget about after the first time they kill him\"?\n\nEdit; Well, now he's a raidboss. Still a big disappointment and a pushover (Killed him with our 10man group, had some newbies tagging along, one-shot him...), but a raidboss, not the penultimate boss of Icecrown, but still... HE'S A FRIGGING RAID BOSS, YES!:(\n*Goes over to hoping the penultimate boss is a mix of Four Horsemen, Illidari Council and High King Maulgar, with Anub'arak, Prince Kael'Thas, The Black Knight and Baron Rivendare*", "date": "2008-10-03T14:07:24-05:00", "rating": 36, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Swapping the names would solve siad problem, but I doubt Blizzard would do such a thing. By lore, he is indeed an equal to Vashj and Kael, if not stronger (After all, Anub'arak did destroy the Army of the Illdari, as Arthas was a tad busy with Illidian and the Obelisks...) Epic fail making him a 5man.  On a side note, tiss and epic fail killing off all the Scourge characters. Some of us liked that WC3 team...  But, as always, the policy is \"lol lore\" as we all know, so our bitching will be downrated and purged. Perhaps a petition on WoW Forumns proper. You have my vote for swapping the names o", "creationdate": "2008-10-03T14:07:25-05:00", "id": 356168, "rating": 41, "commentid": 395631, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "163531", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "My toughts exactly - I was expecting an Ice Crown level boss. What annoys me most at this point is that this could be made a lot less painful by simply swapping the names of Anub'arak and Anub'rekhan - It wouldn't be the Icecrown level place he deserves but atleast he'd be in raid level content.", "creationdate": "2008-10-09T07:37:08-05:00", "id": 49843, "rating": 34, "commentid": 395631, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nagassh", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-09-09T15:58:57-05:00", 1, "Ingolfur"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 421822, "nreplies": 10, "sticky": 0, "user": "33463", "body": "How it should work out...\r\nAnub guards a chest of loot in his lair.\r\nPlayers encounter Anub in 5-man.\r\nPlayers beat Anub to 3% life.\r\nArthas appears and separates the players from Anub before he is slain.\r\nArthas exchanges some dialog to Anub about how loyal he has been to Arthas.\r\nArthas buys Anub time to burrow and escape the encounter.\r\nArthas gives one last line about fighing a stronger Anub later on....\r\nPlayers open chest, receive loot.\r\nPlayers anticipate a raid-level boss Anub in the future.", "date": "2008-10-27T08:32:20-05:00", "rating": 114, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yeah, only Anub'Arak hates the Lich King's guts :/  Evidenced in [url=http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/info/underdev/1p11/roadtodamnation.html]Road to Damnation[/url]  (\"The nerubian race, yes. Then the master came. As his influence spread, we made war upon him, foolishly believing we stood a chance. Many of us were slain and raised into undeath. In life I was a king. Today I am a crypt lord.\"  \"In return for immortality, you agreed to serve him,\" Kel'Thuzad mused aloud. Remarkable.  \"'Agreed' implies choice.\")   and his instance quotes (\"Ahhh... RAAAAAGH! Never thought... I would be free of him", "creationdate": "2008-10-27T08:32:21-05:00", "id": 374332, "rating": 27, "commentid": 421822, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "51581", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I agree, he could escape just like Mal'ganis does in CoT:Stratholme, but only to re-appear in a high-end raid.", "creationdate": "2008-12-02T13:51:26-06:00", "id": 61280, "rating": 10, "commentid": 421822, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "255649", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You are forgetting about the Lich King's endgame. He lets you kill Anub'arak so that you can be stronger for it - so that you may in turn serve him once he decides to force you into his servitude.  He fully expects to win, in the end.", "creationdate": "2009-03-17T12:57:36-05:00", "id": 86024, "rating": 7, "commentid": 421822, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "78213", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It would be nice if Anub could call his minions at around 5%, so they swarm in there like some bug stampede and you lose Anub's target and have to kill every insect so you can get to chest as mentioned above... And everyone gets insect pet from chest that cast poisons on lowbies and hunt down rabbits and deers in front of Stormwind... something like meanie http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32617 ;)   Edit: Lil' typos...", "creationdate": "2009-04-05T09:13:52-05:00", "id": 89483, "rating": 6, "commentid": 421822, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "staan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "\"How it should work out... Anub guards a chest of loot in his lair. Players encounter Anub in 5-man. Players beat Anub to 3% life. Arthas appears and separates the players from Anub before he is slain. Arthas exchanges some dialog to Anub about how loyal he has been to Arthas. Arthas buys Anub time to burrow and escape the encounter. Arthas gives one last line about fighing a stronger Anub later on.... Players open chest, receive loot. Players anticipate a raid-level boss Anub in the future.\"  BLIZZARD, HIRE THIS MAN", "creationdate": "2009-10-19T23:29:23-05:00", "id": 128308, "rating": 10, "commentid": 421822, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "470844", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 425858, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "cassady", "body": "People who don't raid deserve to see epic characters too.  Kargath Bladefist was every bit as deserving of a greater place than a 5-man as Anub'arak is; Rend Blackhand and Balnazzar got the same treatment.", "date": "2008-10-30T19:13:21-05:00", "rating": 30, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "...But Rend was in one of the original ten-man encounters.  One of the first truly difficult encounters when the game was launched.  UBRS was one of the first major raid areas, like, [i]ever[/i].", "creationdate": "2009-01-15T09:14:23-06:00", "id": 72888, "rating": 17, "commentid": 425858, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Tyristrasz", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Rend was a boss in an old 15man that was converted to a 10man of the max level at the time it came out.  Balnazzar was a boss in strath which used to be a 10man when the game first came out.  And Bladefist owns the hardest heroic ever put into WoW.  And what did Anub'arak get? a place in a level 74 dungeons...so dotn even try to compare atleast the others where in max level dungeons.", "creationdate": "2009-02-01T13:08:19-06:00", "id": 77146, "rating": 16, "commentid": 425858, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bany", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "For the record, UBRS used to be a full 40 man instance at release before they limited it to 15 and then 10. At level 57 in mostly greens with a few blues the instance took several hours to clear.", "creationdate": "2009-03-01T02:13:05-06:00", "id": 83026, "rating": 11, "commentid": 425858, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "aleph", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 432136, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "240582", "body": "Remember, Anub'arak is an undead. Perhaps in the Icecrown Citadel raid Arthas will have resurrected Anub'arak again to serve in undeath again, after all Anub'arak has already proved himself as a very good servant (in The Frozen Throne: Legacy of the Damned Campaign.)", "date": "2008-11-05T14:35:48-06:00", "rating": 70, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "[quote=cdpang]But I skinned him and he despawned.[/quote]  Such trivial matters do not prevent [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=13251]other[/url] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=5442]bosses[/url] from [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=30549]coming[/url] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=27018]back[/url], even when decapitated.  Edit: And...   [quote=Psyblade1st]\"Azjol-Nerub was merely a setback!\"[/quote]  QFT. Anub'Arak is [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zZKDV5S1WI0]back next patch[/url]. Note, the audio clips contain a good deal of spoilers... but it does confirm Anub's return at the end", "creationdate": "2008-11-05T14:35:49-06:00", "id": 394550, "rating": 13, "commentid": 432136, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LatroVir", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I don't know why this was rated down. It's a valid point. The Lich King can raise up any of his servants after they die as he sees fit, and I wouldn't be surprised to see Anubie pop back up in Icecrown, born again.", "creationdate": "2008-11-14T09:59:06-06:00", "id": 55973, "rating": 37, "commentid": 432136, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Erlinn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "But I skinned him and he despawned.", "creationdate": "2008-12-09T21:04:04-06:00", "id": 63422, "rating": 83, "commentid": 432136, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "63902", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[i]Only to rise again.[/i]  Skinless.", "creationdate": "2008-12-22T01:32:08-06:00", "id": 66760, "rating": 64, "commentid": 432136, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "yarai", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "\"Azjol-Nerub was merely a setback!\"", "creationdate": "2009-02-04T10:08:53-06:00", "id": 77833, "rating": 36, "commentid": 432136, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Psyblade1st", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
