{"commentv2": 1, "number": 73, "id": 706465, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "124017", "body": "Dredmon:[quote]If ranged/healer classes stand directly behind him they will get pounded when you turn him, so they should always fight to his side.[/quote]\r\n\r\nTo clarify, Pound is cast in the direction Anub'arak was facing when he began casting. However, to quote a point made by Klakk further down:\r\n\r\n[quote]Run through him when he starts to cast; he'll turn around but the attack won't.[/quote]\r\n\r\nSo I think what Dredmon is saying is that if the tank turns the boss around to avoid Pound, the ranged/healer classes should [i]not[/i] then try to get behind the boss because they'll actually be [i]in range[/i] of Pound, even though they'd technically be standing behind him.\r\n\r\nEither stay put and hope the tank didn't turn the boss too early, or stand to the side to avoid all confusion/uncertainty.", "date": "2009-05-05T14:10:26-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
