{"commentv2": 1, "number": 91, "id": 800548, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "nyctric", "body": "I swear I am one of the only tanks on Proudmoore that aren't retarded and move out of the pound. Even when I'm DPSing I'm like \"Tanks, you can avoid the pound simply by running through him because he is in a fixed position while he casts it so he won't move\" and they're like \"Yep, ok.\" They're still retarded and stay in it. Unable to move for a long time, taking heavy damage and DPS slowly peeling threat back.\r\nTo all the tanks on Proudmoore - get out of the f***ing pound.\r\nAwesome boss and glad to see he's coming back in 3.2.", "date": "2009-08-06T07:22:39-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Pretty much the only way to get rage on this fight with Ulduar/Coliseum gear is to stand in pound.", "creationdate": "2009-08-28T12:49:08-05:00", "id": 118895, "rating": 0, "commentid": 800548, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bikkin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "oh really? ok what is your tanks name? i play on proudmoore as well and i don't stand in the pound, don't sterotype me with the other tanks...", "creationdate": "2009-09-01T17:23:08-05:00", "id": 423105, "rating": 0, "commentid": 800548, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wolverrine", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 92, "id": 805701, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Prada", "body": "Anub'arak: a boss who contradicts himself on so many levels that even Bill O'Reilly worships him as king.\r\n\r\nNerubian: Look, brothers! The [b][i]traitor[/i] [/b]king! (upon seeing Anub'arak) \r\nArthas: Who? Me? \r\nAnub'arak: He is referring to me, death knight. \r\n\r\nKel'Thuzad: In return for immortality, you agreed to serve him. Remarkable.\r\nAnub'arak: 'Agreed' implies choice. \r\n\r\nDeath in Azjol Nerub: Ahhh... RAAAAAGH! Never thought... I would be free of him...\r\n\r\nDeath in Coliseum: I have failed you, master...\r\n\r\nI can almost imagine Arthas playing Katy Perry's \"Hot & Cold\" song to Anub'arak just to make a point.\r\n\r\nAs deliberately sufferable as that may be to Anub'arak, of course.", "date": "2009-08-09T23:06:03-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Does he contradict himself maybe he wasn't completely mind controlled during Azjol nerub like sir zeliek but then once you kill him he's free but then say Arthas strolls on in and brings him back from the dead completely mind controlled then boom he goes under coliseum and you fight him", "creationdate": "2009-08-14T19:05:20-05:00", "id": 420524, "rating": 0, "commentid": 805701, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "falconeye246", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
